Diverse viewpoints and ideas may lead to more innovative and effective decision making when brought to a group or organization via diversity. Additionally, it may aid in promoting inclusion and reducing prejudice and bias. On the other side, variety may create obstacles such as communication hurdles and a lack of understanding of other cultures and backgrounds. Diversity is more likely to be advantageous in business and research settings where problem-solving and creativity are essential. In instances where a varied population is serviced, such as in healthcare or education, it is also likely to be helpful. In instances when a homogenous group is required for operational efficiency or safety, such as in a military unit or medical surgical team, variety may be less advantageous. 